hh3cRaid.name: hh3cRaid
hh3cRaid.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cRaid.description: This MIB describes the general information of raid.

hh3cPrimaryRaidCount.name: hh3cPrimaryRaidCount
hh3cPrimaryRaidCount.description: This object identifies the maximal number of primary raids supported.

hh3cRaidTable.name: hh3cRaidTable
hh3cRaidTable.description: This table containing some property information of the array.

hh3cRaidEntry.name: hh3cRaidEntry
hh3cRaidEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to create array resource.

hh3cRaidName.name: hh3cRaidName
hh3cRaidName.description: This object identifies the name of the array.

hh3cRaidId.name: hh3cRaidId
hh3cRaidId.description: This object describes the identification of the array.

hh3cRaidUuid.name: hh3cRaidUuid
hh3cRaidUuid.description: This object describes the UUID of the array.

hh3cRaidLevel.name: hh3cRaidLevel
hh3cRaidLevel.description: This object identifies the type of array. The value 'jbod' means just a bunch of disks, the value 'raid0' means RAID Level 0, and so on.

hh3cRaidTimestamp.name: hh3cRaidTimestamp
hh3cRaidTimestamp.description: This object identifies the system time when the array is created.

hh3cRaidDiskList.name: hh3cRaidDiskList
hh3cRaidDiskList.description: This object describes a list of the disk composed the array, each two bytes with network-byte order means a single entity index of the disk.

hh3cRaidOwner.name: hh3cRaidOwner
hh3cRaidOwner.description: This object identifies the owner of the array.

hh3cRaidSize.name: hh3cRaidSize
hh3cRaidSize.description: This object describes the size of array's total space. The units is million bytes.

hh3cRaidFreeSize.name: hh3cRaidFreeSize
hh3cRaidFreeSize.description: This object describes the size of array's vacancy space. The units is million bytes.

hh3cRaidAutoSync.name: hh3cRaidAutoSync
hh3cRaidAutoSync.description: This object identifies if the raid should be synchro automatically when created.

hh3cRaidRowStatus.name: hh3cRaidRowStatus
hh3cRaidRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to crate or delete an array.

hh3cRaidManageTable.name: hh3cRaidManageTable
hh3cRaidManageTable.description: This table containing some management information of the array.

hh3cRaidManageEntry.name: hh3cRaidManageEntry
hh3cRaidManageEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to particular array resource.

hh3cRaidLocationState.name: hh3cRaidLocationState
hh3cRaidLocationState.description: This object identifies if the array can be located.

hh3cRaidAction.name: hh3cRaidAction
hh3cRaidAction.description: This object identifies the actions to operating the array. When read, this object always returns the value 'invalid'.

hh3cRaidRunState.name: hh3cRaidRunState
hh3cRaidRunState.description: This object identifies the state of the array. The value 'normal' means array works well. The value 'degraded' means array has degraded. The value 'failed' means some disks met failure and array has failed.

hh3cRaidAutoRebuild.name: hh3cRaidAutoRebuild
hh3cRaidAutoRebuild.description: This object identifies if the array can be auto rebuild.

hh3cRaidSyncPercentage.name: hh3cRaidSyncPercentage
hh3cRaidSyncPercentage.description: This object describes the percentage of progress when the array is synchronizing. The value is equal to '100' when the progress has finished.

hh3cRaidHideState.name: hh3cRaidHideState
hh3cRaidHideState.description: This object identifies if the array is hided. When the value of this object is equal to 'enable', the array will be hided and the files on it can not be accessed by any user.

hh3cRaidLvRestore.name: hh3cRaidLvRestore
hh3cRaidLvRestore.description: This object identifies an action to restore all the logic volume resources.

hh3cRaidType.name: hh3cRaidType
hh3cRaidType.description: This object identifies the physical type of an array. The value 'virtualDevice' means if a array is prepared for virtual device, it can be used to create LV, for exampe, it is can be split into a lot of LV, or be a part of LV. The value 'directDevice' means if a array is prepared for direct device, it can be used to create a LV which type is direct. Unlike virtual devices, they cannot be combined or split into multiple logical devices. The value 'serviceEnabledDevice' means if a array is prepared for service-enabled device, it can be used to create a LV which type is service-enabled. Unlike virtual devices, they cannot be combined or split into multiple logical devices. The value 'unassigned' means it is the original status of a array, if a array is unassigned, it can't be used to create LV.

hh3cRaidCacheTable.name: hh3cRaidCacheTable
hh3cRaidCacheTable.description: This table containing some property information and management information of the array cache.

hh3cRaidCacheEntry.name: hh3cRaidCacheEntry
hh3cRaidCacheEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to particular array cache resource.

hh3cRaidReadCache.name: hh3cRaidReadCache
hh3cRaidReadCache.description: This object identifies the state of read cache. If the value of this object is set to 'disable', the associated percentage of cache hit may be invalid.

hh3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod.name: hh3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod
hh3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod.description: This object describes the period during which how often the date matched with the cache when read. The units is minute.

hh3cRaidReadCacheAverageRate.name: hh3cRaidReadCacheAverageRate
hh3cRaidReadCacheAverageRate.description: This object describes the average percentage of cache hit when read.

hh3cRaidReadCachePhaseRate.name: hh3cRaidReadCachePhaseRate
hh3cRaidReadCachePhaseRate.description: This object describes the percentage of cache hit when read during the period set by the hh3cRaidReadCacheHitPeriod object.

hh3cRaidWriteCache.name: hh3cRaidWriteCache
hh3cRaidWriteCache.description: This object identifies the state of write cache. If the value of this object is set to 'disable', the associated percentage of cache hit may be invalid.

hh3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod.name: hh3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod
hh3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod.description: This object describes the period during which how often the date matched with the cache when writed. The units is minute.

hh3cRaidWriteCacheAverageRate.name: hh3cRaidWriteCacheAverageRate
hh3cRaidWriteCacheAverageRate.description: This object describes the average percentage of cache hit when writed.

hh3cRaidWriteCachePhaseRate.name: hh3cRaidWriteCachePhaseRate
hh3cRaidWriteCachePhaseRate.description: This object describes the percentage of cache hit when write during the period set by the hh3cRaidWriteCacheHitPeriod object.

hh3cRaidWriteCacheFlush.name: hh3cRaidWriteCacheFlush
hh3cRaidWriteCacheFlush.description: This object identifies an action to flushing the write cache.

hh3cRaidSpareDiskTable.name: hh3cRaidSpareDiskTable
hh3cRaidSpareDiskTable.description: This table described the spare hot disk information.

hh3cRaidSpareDiskEntry.name: hh3cRaidSpareDiskEntry
hh3cRaidSpareDiskEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a spare hot disk.

hh3cRaidSpareDiskRowStatus.name: hh3cRaidSpareDiskRowStatus
hh3cRaidSpareDiskRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to create or delete spare hot disk.

hh3cFreezeRaidTable.name: hh3cFreezeRaidTable
hh3cFreezeRaidTable.description: This table described the freezed raid management.

hh3cFreezeRaidEntry.name: hh3cFreezeRaidEntry
hh3cFreezeRaidEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to manage the freezed raid.

hh3cFreezeRaidUuid.name: hh3cFreezeRaidUuid
hh3cFreezeRaidUuid.description: This object describes the uuid of the freezed raid.

hh3cFreezeRaidName.name: hh3cFreezeRaidName
hh3cFreezeRaidName.description: This object describes the name of the freezed raid.

hh3cFreezeRaidRowStatus.name: hh3cFreezeRaidRowStatus
hh3cFreezeRaidRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to manage the freezed raid. Only the value 'destroy' is supported.

hh3c3rdRaidTable.name: hh3c3rdRaidTable
hh3c3rdRaidTable.description: This table described the 3rd raid management.

hh3c3rdRaidEntry.name: hh3c3rdRaidEntry
hh3c3rdRaidEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to manage the 3rd raid.

hh3c3rdRaidUuid.name: hh3c3rdRaidUuid
hh3c3rdRaidUuid.description: This object describes the uuid of the 3rd raid.

hh3c3rdRaidName.name: hh3c3rdRaidName
hh3c3rdRaidName.description: This object describes the name of the 3rd raid.

hh3c3rdRaidOwner.name: hh3c3rdRaidOwner
hh3c3rdRaidOwner.description: This object describes the owner of the 3rd raid.

hh3c3rdRaidImport.name: hh3c3rdRaidImport
hh3c3rdRaidImport.description: This object describes the owner for the 3rd raid. When read, the value 'none' will be get. If the action is executed successfully, the 3rd raid will become a primary raid, and this entry will be deleted automatically.

hh3c3rdRaidRowStatus.name: hh3c3rdRaidRowStatus
hh3c3rdRaidRowStatus.description: This object describes the actions to manage the 3rd raid. Only the value 'destroy' is supported.
